  "body": "There are many tests in the repo that have multiple expect() assertions in the same `it` block which requires inspecting byline which assertion failed. See example:\r\nhttps://github.com/ChainSafe/lodestar/blob/298354baa70a537d6f12a946e078d8810be563a6/packages/lodestar/test/unit/api/impl/beacon/blocks/publishBlock.test.ts#L56-L57\r\n\r\n```\r\n@chainsafe/lodestar:   1 failing\r\n@chainsafe/lodestar:   1) api - beacon - publishBlock\r\n@chainsafe/lodestar:          successful publish:\r\n@chainsafe/lodestar:      AssertionError: expected false not to be true\r\n```\r\n\r\nInstead, we could add some metadata or extect message such as:\r\n\r\n```ts\r\nexpect(chainStub.receiveBlock.calledOnceWith(block), \"receiveBlock not called once with block\").to.be.true;\r\nexpect(gossipStub.publishBlock.calledOnceWith(block), \"publishBlock not called once with block\").to.be.true;  \r\n```\r\n\r\n```\r\n@chainsafe/lodestar:   1 failing\r\n@chainsafe/lodestar:   1) api - beacon - publishBlock\r\n@chainsafe/lodestar:          successful publish:\r\n@chainsafe/lodestar:      AssertionError: receiveBlock not called once with block\r\n```\r\n",
